 \lim_{t\to0}\frac1t\left(f(x)^t-1\right)=\log(f(x)) 
 \begin{align} \lim_{t\to0}\left(\int_0^1f(x)^t\,\mathrm{d}x\right)^{1/t} &=\lim_{t\to0}\left(1+t\int_0^1\frac1t\left(f(x)^t-1\right)\,\mathrm{d}x\right)^{1/t}\\ &=\lim_{t\to0}\left(1+t\int_0^1\log\left(f(x)\right)\,\mathrm{d}x\right)^{1/t}\\[6pt] &=e^{\int_0^1\log\left(f(x)\right)\,\mathrm{d}x} \end{align} 
